Ichigo Kurosaki is a rather normal high school student apart from the fact he has the ability to see ghosts. This ability never impacted his life in a major way until the day he encounters the Shinigami Kuchiki Rukia, who saves him and his family's lives from a Hollow, a corrupt spirit that devours human souls.
Wounded during the fight against the Hollow, Rukia chooses the only option available to defeat the monster and passes her Shinigami powers to Ichigo. Now forced to act as a substitute until Rukia recovers, Ichigo hunts down the Hollows that plague his town.
Ore dake Level Up na Ken

They say whatever doesnt kill you makes you stronger, but thats not the case for the worlds weakest hunter Seong Jin-U. After being brutally slaughtered by monsters in a high-ranking dungeon, Jin-U came back with the System, a program only he could see, thats leveling him up in every way. Now, hes inspired to discover the secrets behind his powers and the dungeon that spawned them.
(Source: Crunchyroll)

What would the world be like if 80 percent of the population manifested extraordinary superpowers called Quirks at age four? Heroes and villains would be battling it out everywhere! Becoming a hero would mean learning to use your power, but where would you go to study? U.A. High's Hero Program of course! But what would you do if you were one of the 20 percent who were born Quirkless?
Middle school student Izuku Midoriya wants to be a hero more than anything, but he hasn't got an ounce of power in him. With no chance of ever getting into the prestigious U.A. High School for budding heroes, his life is looking more and more like a dead end. Then an encounter with All Might, the greatest hero of them all gives him a chance to change his destiny
(Source: Viz Media)

Daniel is an unattractive loner who wakes up in a different body. Now tall, handsome, and cooler than ever in his new form, Daniel aims to achieve everything he couldn't before. How far will he go to keep his body... and his secrets? (Source: WEBTOON)

In a world where awakened beings called Hunters must battle deadly monsters to protect humanity, Seong Jin-U, nicknamed the weakest hunter of all mankind, finds himself in a constant struggle for survival. One day, after a brutal encounter in an overpowered dungeon wipes out his party and threatens to end his life, a mysterious System chooses him as its sole player: Jin-U has been granted the rare opportunity to level up his abilities, possibly beyond any known limits. Follow Jin-Us journey as he takes on ever-stronger enemies, both human and monster, to discover the secrets deep within the dungeons and the ultimate extent of his powers. (Source: Tappytoon) Note: Includes 22 extra chapters.

Once the bullies target you, its game over. The school is run by tyrants whose favorite hobby is tormenting the weakest kids in class. But then Gray arrived. This mysterious new student threatens to dismantle the established order. He may be small in stature, but his calculative and brutal fighting leaves unsuspecting opponents lying on the floor begging for mercy. Now the school's toughest bullies have to scramble to take down this new and unusual hero. (Source: WEBTOON)
Ookami wa Tsuki ni Koi wo Suru

Ryuna Kamikawa is the beautiful and perfect-acting student council president. When she gets angry at her lazy vice-president, Yugi Tsukiyama, he likes to tease her by calling "wolf-senpai."

The two are like the light and dark sides of the moon, total opposites who don't get along. Until one day, when Tsukiyama discovers the hidden side of "Wolf Senpai" through his secret part-time job...?

This is the start of a love story between two people with hidden identities!

(Source: Ura Sunday, translated)

Akira returns to the countryside for high school with a plan to win the heart of her childhood crush! They're both fools in love because she's too dense to figure out he likes her back! (Source: Viz Media)
Osoraku Kanojo wa Ore no Aniki wo Neratteru

A high school guy who doesn't trust girls anymore has been tricked too many times by girls who just wanted to get close to his good-looking older brother. After all that, he decides hell never trust a girl again.
But then, a pretty girl in his class suddenly starts talking to him a lot. Is she just trying to get to his brother too? Or does she actually mean something else? (Source: Manga Park, translated)
